ratings.rComments: Very good professor. Explains things in a very clear and simple manner. He has a good attitude and can be pretty funny in class. This class is very test heavy, the three midterms and final count for 75% of the class and yes the tests are hard. However, there is a decent curve on all tests.  Would recommend.
Great professor, fun guy, tests are hard. He really makes you put in the effort. He truly is "Tricky Tom".

Tests are a little tricky but not a problem after going through the practice versions. Prof. Hummel is especially helpful when you have specific question. He will make it short and clear and explain to you patiently if you're still confused. And you can make money by correcting his mistakes during the lecture. Nice professor, enjoyed his class.
Easy class,

I really enjoyed having Tricky Tom. His class wasn't exactly easy but he is an excellent teacher. Grade is very test-oriented and you won't get a good one unless you prepare for his exams, which are...... tricky. There is always a time crunch for these exams but this does not take anything away from his actual teaching ability. Take him if able to.

His tests are very challenging. You must prepare yourself by reading the material and doing a ton of practice problems from the book. I also did past quizzes which can be found at the chemistry learning center on campus.
Tough class. Need to pay close attention in lectures. Definitely go to discussion and ask questions.

Professor Hummel is a funny guy and an efficient, effective lecturer. His exams are a bit longer than the other professors' exams and perhaps involve more exceptions than normal (hence the name "Tricky Tom"). Nevertheless, if you are going to lecture, doing the homework problems, and studying for exams, you'll do well (he adjusts grade cutoffs).

Hummel is very difficult. Because of the large lecture, help needs to be sought out personally. But Hummel gives it if you ask. His TAs were not helpful. His exams are difficult: more questions than any other CHEM 102 professor's tests and less time to complete them. It almost always is a race to finish before running out of time. AVOID IF POSSIBLE
Pretty fair. You get out what you put in.

Great lecturer. However, there's a reason his nickname is Tricky Tom, and that is because the tests are really hard. However, if you go to his office hours, he is there for you and will help you succeed.
Very passionate teacher. Always gives specific answers to questions. Treats students with respect.

If you need help understanding a topic, go to Office Hours. He is very good and willing to explain the little details to you then, which may not have been possible during the lecture. He like to blow stuff up and do chemistry experiments so that was always really fun to watch. DO ALL THE TEXT BOOK HOMEWORK AND PRACTICE EXAMS QUESTIONS!

So-so section. Since CHEM102 is just a elementary course. Just consider the clarity and performance of him. It's not bad. Textbook is required because there are writing assignments based on textbook on his section.
He does a really good job of answering questions that anybody has during the lectures
His lecture is really amazing.

I loved having Tricky Tom! He's an amazing lecturer and really knows his stuff, but the tests are kinda tough. I took this class over the summer so the class load was also crazy fast. He definitely wants you to learn, and will answer any questions you have, and will even give out money to those who catch mistakes or answer questions in lecture.

I probably skipped his lecture once a week and still ended up with an A. Hummel is a pretty good lecturer but Tim my TA was also really good at explaining so I learn from both of them. Hummel gives me a glimpse of what the topic is about and Tim explains the topic during discussion.  Overall, Hummel is a great professor! His explanations are clear.

Tom Hummel is a great, great lecturer who has a clear understanding of chemistry. Unfortunately, his tests are very hard. He is very approachable if you have questions, and he's pretty funny, which makes lectures interesting. The class was curved quite a bit, so the impossible tests aren't too bad, but they are hard. Not much homework, so study.

Tom was a great lecturer. He obviously knew his material, and he was always there for his students. Yeah, his exams can be tough. However, the format of these exams are almost identical to the practice exams and the homework problems. If you really practice those two materials, you should be set for the exams.
He takes pride in having low exam averages and actively tries to trick students with his exam questions.

Hummel is a tale of two extremes in ways. He's a good lecturer.  He speaks clearly, and is generally liked by the student. He also has a self-imposed nickname of "Tricky Tom" due to his love and affinity for throwing a few curveballs in his exams. If you study the practice tests, he's definitely a manageable professor.

Tom was a very nice professor who was willing to help, but his class was very difficult. His tests are hard, and require a deep understanding of the lectures. Pay attention in class and ask lots of questions!

I loved having Tom. Lecture are simple and fast. His exams can be hard but most of the questions already showed up in past exams and in lectures. He is very humble and respectful of his students; great guy and a great professor.
He's very knowledgeable and wants you to learn, but the tests are unnecessarily difficult. He is very passionate, so lectures are educational and interesting.
Very difficult tests, but he teaches well.

Unless you REALLY like chemistry, I suggest taking Chem 102 with someone else. A good teacher, but expects you to have a strong passion for chemistry even though most people are taking the class to fulfill some requirement in their major. Good teacher, but tests are some of the hardest I've ever taken.

A good lecturer, but makes the exams like he is a mad man. Do not take this class if u want A good grade. It's like makes the test just to make u get a bad grade in the class. In general bad teaching philosophy.

I think Professor is funny and he is a great teacher. If you are interested in chemistry and you want to test whether you have a great foundation in chemistry before, I think you should take his class. I know that the quiz and the tests are obviously hard, but if you could make it through, it will be great chance to have a solid chemistry foundatio
Really good professor. Exams are a little bit hard but if you work hard and do practice exams you can get good grades.

He is an awesome lecturer. Even though the class moves at a fast pace (no matter whose class you're in) his lectures are comprehensive and interesting. Also, attending lecture is important unless you're a genius.  And do your homework.
The class is difficult but by going to class you will be sorted
Tough exams
Very helpful and wants to help students learn material. However, tests are a beotch. Make sure to use practice exams and do ALL of the homework assigned, no matter if it's graded or not.
Don't take this class unless you absolutely need to. Screwed over my GPA.

The tests were terrible. I'm not a chem major and I guess I'm not very good at chem, but I studied a decent amount. I always felt like it was a guessing game and I just hoped I guessed more right answers than everyone else.

How to get an A in chem 102 w Hummel: do most homework problems BEFORE lecture and go over them again before quizzes, go to every lecture as he gives hints on exam content, do every old hour exam available (including older ones in the chem learning center), go to office hours consistently. all gen chem classes are hard regardless of the prof

tried deliberately to trick you on tests. tests are written to be hard, not to check that you understand most of the material. if you don't know every trick and exception, you will not do well on the tests. lectures were fast and very confusing; he just does calculations on the board and expects you to follow them. studied a lot, idk if i'll pass
I'd say he was your average professor. Difficult, but not overly so. I think he was very effective at teaching in lectures. His exams and quizzes were a bit harder than they needed to be.

Very difficult class to come away with an A compared to every other chem class. Tests are not a true test of knowledge but rather a test to overcome his unknown tricks to throw off students. "Past exams" are not indicative of current ones. I got an A raw score on practice exams but low B's on current exams. He WANTS to trick you. Take another prof.

I don't know how he has a good rating. He make Chem much harder than it has to be in order to curve it however he wants. When the average on the exams is barely over 50% you're doing something wrong. Everyone that I have this with is miserable because of him, and when compared to other Chem 102 classes, the exams seem impossible. Don't take him.
Get the practice exam book. The actual exams are very similar.

His nickname may be Tricky Tom, but I definitely think he was the best CHEM 102 professor to have. The tests are very difficult, but are subsequently curved. If you have not taken AP Chem, you need to put in effort to do well. It's not impossible, but don't go thinking you can coast through the class. Great Professor. Funny guy too!
AWESOME. He's hard, but it's so worth it. Best teacher I've had

He's a good professor, but his tests can be difficult (even for a student that did well in AP Chem). There are a lot of subtle things he does to make the exams tricky (earning him the nick name, "Tricky Tom").  However, paying attention in class, doing the homework, and studying by looking over lecture notes and taking past exams is very helpful.

The tests are very rushed but practicing with the past exams is the best thing you can do.  Tom is a little fast in lecture but he is a really nice guy who wants you to do well.  Make an effort to see him during his office hours.

Hummel is a really great professor. People always complain about how difficult his class is, but if you put in the effort, you will do well. Do ALL of the homework problems, not just the evens. Go to his office hours! He genuinely wants to help students and doesn't "dumb down" the material. Class is hard, but I learned so much in just one semester.

He's very smart and knows his field very well. They call him Tricky Tom for a reason though, and you have to be proficient at the material as exams are pretty difficult. Usually, if you can figure out what each question is testing, you should be good. My advice -PRACTICE! Do ALL practice problems and past exams! Many questions are similar.

This was easily the hardest class I had all semester, but it was my mistake that I didn't treat it as such! If you are looking for an easy time with Tricky Tom then you are mistaken! Take your homework seriously and STUDYSTUDYSTUDY, then you have a good chance with his tests. And know your stuff well. He really is tricky!

Very good professor. It is very clear that he knows his stuff and is always helpful to students. Encourages students to ask questions in lecture and overall wants to see his students learn and do very well. I definitely recommend u to take him as your professor

Tricky Tom, as he refers to himself, was very difficult. I have never had to work harder in a class. I even had to hire a tutor. That being said, compared to other teachers he was the best of choice. He works with you throughout the semester and scales everything. Because of that, I brought by C- to a B by the end of the semester.

It's a class worth your time. As long as you keep with with his lectures and the discussion classes on a regular basis, it's a straight forward A for this class. He's very helpful when it comes to his office hours. Quizes, Hour Exams and Finals are curved reasonably.

Tricky Tom was probably the best professor I had all semester. He goes through material quickly at times, so I personally found it helpful to read the book before attending lecture. The entire class is curved, which makes his harder tests much more reasonable.

He is so enthusiastic about chemistry, and I respect him for trying so hard to motivate his students. However, the tests were so extremely hard. If you can't do the hardest homework problems in the book, then you are bound to struggle in this class. Luckily he curves the tests and quizzes. I wished I would have learned more.
Easy

Probably the best teacher I have had while at this university. Everyone says he is super hard, but it pays off in the end because you are able to grab a firm understanding of Chemistry, which really helps if you have to continue taking Chemistry for a major or minor. :) Choose him and you will be fine. The tests are curved, so that's always nice.

He's passionate about chemistry but too fast in lectures. He'll answer questions without being condescending. He'll even give students money for catching mistakes in class. Exams are impossible and test your rate of completion, not what you actually know.  Exams will be 35 questions with 19 difficult calculations in 70 minutes. You must study!

Professor Hummel is what everyone calls him. He even nickname's himself "Tricky Tom." However, he is one of the best professors I have ever had. His exams are made for the top chem students. However, if you do all the work, it is possible to succeed in his class. Plus, he preforms in lecture demonstrations!

Tom Hummel is many things but easy is not one of them. He is a very competent lecturer, and if you use the Chem learning center, and his office hours, it is possible to succeed is his course. You really have to work for an A, because his exams are very difficult. You will learn alot because you must master the material to perform on the tests.

His lecture is clear. However he tends to go a bit faster. Discussion section is the most helpful if you take his section. Exams are hard and mainly dominated with thinking questions. A if you are expert of all the theories and fast in thinking to solve multiple tricky MCQs. However his class has a curve around 68%. Firm foundation -> choose him.

If you have him, GET OUT. He's an average lecturer, but his tests are VERY HARD. He calls himself tricky tom, and there is a reason why he does. It is nice if you do all the questions assigned for homework because he did write the questions for the book, but it's not worth it.

Hummell was a great lecturer if you read prior to attending class. Keeping up with readings, paying attention in lecture, and doing homework and practice exams should get you a good grade. The exams are only tricky if you don't do the suggested problems and practice exams.

Prof. Hummel definitely deserves the title "Tricky Tom." His exams were very challenging because of hard problems and a short amount of time. However, he was extremely helpful, nice, and good at listening during office hours. If you work hard, you can get a good grade in his class
His tests were very hard, and pushed the time limit frequently. You will learn a lot, however, if you don't want to work for your grade, don't take this professor!
Way too hard, you'll learn a hell of a lot compared to the other teachers but the gpa drop is brutal. His tests are pointlessly hard.

If you're looking for the easiest professor, don't go for Hummel. However Hummel will get you interested in Chem. His Exam questions are tough, its all about understanding the material and applying it to questions you might not have even seen. If you don't like Chem even just a little, I wouldn't recommend  taking Chem with him.
Yes his tests are hard, but you learn so much in his class. Go to his office hours; he's extremely helpful! He's also a character in the classroom.
His tests are hard, but in reality, I learned so much in his class. Office Hours are also very helpful because it is one on one help. Best Chem Teacher I ever Had!
Hard as heck, if you get him, get out now. the exams are impossible.

He's a pretty good teacher. I hate chemistry, but he at least made it less annoying than it could have been. He's blunt about stuff and he'll help you out if you ask. Tests are hard, but if you have a good TA, you can figure out at least how to pass them.

Great professor, but somewhat difficult. Makes lectures entertaining and gives out dollar bills, which is an incentive to paying attention. His lecture notes are helpful and the past hour exams are indicative of exam type questions he puts on his tests.
Difficult professor, but tries to make class fun. He is actually pretty funny. Doing the homework and studying regularly will get you a decent grade. Never slack off! It gets hard at the end.
He goes deep into new materials very quickly. Exams are very detailed. I suggest you to have a decent background of chemistry before taking his class.
awful professor, he is funny but i ended up getting a C in the class because he makes everything so confusing. save yourself the stress and take it with a different professor

He is a difficult professor, however he makes class at least fun.  Cracks a lot of jokes which lightens the mood and keeps you interested in the class.  Do the homework assignments and study and you will do well. I would recommend buying his lecture notes, they are very helpful.

wayyyy too difficult of a class for being a 100 level course. I attended every lecture and discussion, and i'm still struggling. Tom is really nice and funny, but his tests are RIDICULOUS. he gives a lot of homework too, which is helpful but excessive. i would not recommend him as a professor.
helpful and clear. difficulty level was quite standard. fun class even if you don't like chemistry very much

Professor Hummel is a great professor and I enjoyed him a lot. His exams aren't necessarily hard, but very detailed (most would say tricky). Well, that's why he nicknamed himself tricky Tom. Fair curves on exams and quizzes. Lon-capa based homework not too bad. Overall, a good and fair professor.

Was an enjoyable lecture, not required. I had taken AP Chemistry, so that made the class much easier. It's pretty much all in the notes packet that he puts on sale, then goes over during the lecture. TA's are helpful and there is a quiz every week. Tests aren't bad, but he likes to pay attention to small details.

Tom has an enjoyable lecture, granted im a chem major, but i think he is funny. He presents material well and has nice notes available for purchase (be sure to purchase). They call him tricky tom for a reason, he pushes your knowledge on the exams and loves exceptions and small details. Read, study book work and be prepared for exam style.
I loved Tom! This Chem class is actually very fun for me. Tests can be tricky, but not HARD per se. Recommanded :)
Stopped going to lecture two weeks in.  A-
Make sure your TA doesn't suck and you'll do fine.

He is a good professor and generally lets you know what he is looking for on tests. He writes challenging tests, and you never know how you do on the quizzes until after he scales them, but it works out being fare to all discussion sections.
He explains things well and he is humorous! Good professor. I like him :>

Probably one of the easier CHEM 102 professors. Explains things well, and puts a small curve on exams. Puts some sort of modified bell curve on quizzes, though not too sure how that is yet. Knows what he's talking about, and review sessions are helpful.
I hate him. I got an A in Orgo, and a B in HIS class? NOT POSSIBLE. And yes, I worked really hard in his class, so my laziness isn't the issue here. It's HIM.
Some people complain about how tricky he is but if you just keep up with your work, it's not hard at all.  He's a great teacher.

Tricky Tom is named so for a reason... his tests are unbearable, stressful, and downright impossible. Attending lectures is almost pointless because I have so much difficulty paying attention to him. Some of his TAs are low quality too.
Avoid at all costs.  "Tricky Tom" takes pride in writing the most difficult, tricky exam possible.  His tests are harder than other teachers and he assigns more work.  Do not take Hummel.
COnFusing chem material! makes his exams for the top two students! everybody else fails...
Good in lecture, clear, enthusiastic, and helpful outside of class too.

Professor enjoys writing difficult trick questions. Can be very mocking to the point it's hard to tell if it's really just his sense of humor, laughs at students having trouble on exams. Teaches only basics, have to really braincramp to figure test questions, problem is time is too limited. Could have been challenging, but very doable, w/o him.

Tricky Tom has earned this name for a reason. He really tries to confuse you on the exams, but be sure to go to lecture and discussion and you will have a good grade. Try hard and you'll do just fine.

Had him last semester. Good lecturer, if you go to lecture he will explain the material well and answer questions. He's a character and I found him funny. His tests can be pretty hard. The quizzes aren't easy either. Its chem 102, you wont get an A for doing nothing.

My TA gave easier quizes than the rest of the TA's.  Because of this, Hummel decided it would be a good idea to screw us over and lower our grades by 4-5 percent.  Would have had a C but came out with a D+.  Big difference.  Tried to reason with him, wouldnt budge.

A difficult class: come prepared to work and study hard!  Tests are very difficult and can also be hard to study for.  "Tricky Tom" can be very helpful 1-on-1, but only if you have specific questions.
I really liked Professor Hummel for Chemistry 1. He is quite the character. I had a good time in his class. His multiple choice tests are sometimes difficult.

Gives good explanations and always seems happy to answer questions or do more example problems.  Despite his clarity in lecture, his tests do tend to be difficult, though not impossibly so.  Attend lecture and section, and be prepared to do a lot of work, and you can come out of the class with a good grade and a good understanding of the material.
he is tricky and worst prof i ever had, don't take him  if u don't have to .also pick a good ta, ta make the quiz not him.some ta are good, some are really bad. and they trying to low ur grade up

Prof. Hummel is extremely helpful. If you don't understand something during lecture then be sure to go to his office hours. His exams are tricky, but he tries to test his best students. Take his class, you will learn chemistry :)

He's most definitely not a bad professor. He's a nice guy, he explains concepts well in lecture, and he'll answer any questions you have, but his exams are very hard. The kinds of questions he asks on exams are tricky and much more in depth than homework problems or quiz questions, so you really have to put an effort into the class to succeed.
Good professor who told you what he wanted you to learn and then expected you to learn it. Some of the exams were difficult, but they were always curved.

I really enjoyed Hummel's class. His lectures were interesting, and he mixed in demonstrations to keep people involved. The class was not too difficult, but it can be if you do not do the homework problems or do not study for the tests. I would recommend the past exam booklet. I was not looking forward to chem, but I ended up liking the class!

Great professor. Very understanding and his lectures are interesting. He is very laid back with attendance, and is very approachable. Very good guy to go and see if you have a problem or if you are not doing well. The best chem 102 teacher, if not more, just had him in 102. would go out of my way to get him again for sure.
He is a great professor.  He explains all of the concepts clearly and makes good use of the materials he gives out.  His tests are challenging but fair.
He is a really nice professor, and his favorite word is "goofy". I heard stories that he gives money to people who correct him :)
Hes a great teacher but the class is kind of hard! Study and do homework you'll be fine!
Hes a great teacher but the class is kind of hard! Study and do homework you'll be fine!
Good teacher, knows his stuff and communicates concepts well

Professor Hummel is not a great professor only to those who enjoy chemistry. He talks way too fast, does easy example problems in class, and expects you to master problems that he says are designed for the "smartest student." His exams are hard. I recommend that you actually have a good background chemistry before entering this class.
Funny, knows what hes talking about, keeps the students attention
Super fun to listen to when in lecture. Likes to do a lot of different presentations to show what we are learning (especially things that involve explosions).

He definitely lives up to his name as Tricky Tom Hummel, yet is an amazing professor. He truly does have the students best interest at heart. Do not hesitate to go ask him for any questions, he is so helpful. Get to know him, and really put forth a strong effort in his class it will pay off. I had to work very hard to get a B, so don't expect a goo

I came into the class only taking it because it was required for me.  I hated chemistry as it was, and altough "Tricky Tom" could be humorous, I found him really hard to follow because he talked so fast and I had never had any idea what was going on. However I had an awesome TA and that helped alot. But this class sucked for me, and I really tried.
I'm never bored in his lectures!

Great lecturer. Very animated and funny, keeps material interesting. May talk fast at times, but his explanations are great if you keep up. His exams are quite hard, but perfectly possible if you keep up with the material.
He is so funny. He is a good teacher, but you need to study on your own. You need to do practice problems if you want your A. He is extremely nice and approachable.
Hummel is a tough but really good professor and he makes class funny.

I'm laughing about every five minutes in class, and he does a lot of experiments (mostly blowing things up) that are very interesting.  I think he explains things extremely well.  If you're a slacker, you'll have a hard time with the tests.  But if you honestly try, I think an A or B won't be impossible to get.

Reading through most of these comments I would have thought the class wouldn't be too difficult and relatively easy to understand.  After taking the class I thought Hummel talked really fast and the exams were hard. I don't know if most of these people just love chemistry but I do NOT agree with the majority of the very positive student feedback
Everything was clearly explained...straightforward

Tricky Tom is the best! He looks like my uncle! Hes a great professor and has a lot of passion for what he does. The exams are not bad at all- just make sure you take your time and read the questions and you will only get a few wrong! He is hilarious and explains things clearly. Make sure you get a good TA though because Hummel doesnt write them!!
Hummel is the worst teacher I have ever had.  Hard Tests.  Don't take!

Nice guy, some material could use more explaining, but overall good lecture.  Online homework sucks and the tests are very difficult, but curved a lot.  Good TAs help a lot in this class since they write the quizzes and go over lecture stuff.

This was an easy class. The past hour exams are monstrously helpful. His exams have a few tricks in them, but take your time on them and think and they're easy to figure out. Tom made me really like chemistry.

"Tricky" Tom Hummel is an excellent teacher. To succeed, buy the past hours exams and the notes. He makes the material easy to understand and occasionally will let you out early. His exams are actually easy if you read the questions and THINK what it is that is being asked, as well as discerning tricks.
Lots of demos and explosions in class. I thought the class was not too hard but many of my friends struggled a bit. The tests can be tricky but if you know what you're doing they're pretty easy

Excellent lecturer; clear explanations of complicated topics, liberal use of demonstrations. Tests are not too difficult if you study and do the assigned homework. Very personable, easily accessible and extremely helpful, and aware of student's issues.

Be very careful with this class because he is a awesome teacher but his tests are tricky so go to the Chem Learning Center and get a past exam so you can know all his tricks. Also, make sure your T.A. is good because they make the quizes not him. If your T.A. is a person that says he will try to fail you, that means get a new T.A
He is a pretty cool teacher but his tests are really hard.

The exams are not too bad he will try and trick and put the mistake answers on the exam, but he warns of this many times in class.  He does a lot of demos, for example on the last day of class he devoted half the class to redox reactions which were all cool.  Don't fall behind in reading, going to class helps, get old hour exam book helps a lot.
He seems to want his students to fail...

This class is difficult but not impossible. You have to work for your grade. Most people do bad on the exams and then they get curved some. Important to review practice exams because they are similar to the real exams. Good luck.
Hey y'all...try to go to parkland to take this class...unless you are urgently need for this class.

Do yourself a favor: get a different professor. Hummel makes his exams hard on purpose, and he often tests on exceptions. I very frequently felt as though he was trying to trick us with the exams to see if we read one line on one page, instead of trying to see if we knew general chemistry. Take a lect/disc session with a TA 4days/week if you can.
Tests are overly difficult to make you do poorly!

Not that easy, but an excellent teacher. I had to work very hard for this class. BUY THE RECOMMENDED NOTES! They help alot. Also, take alot of side notes in the notes packet. If you want an A, you have to do ALL of the homework assignments. Or, you could be a genius. Either way, he is definately one of the best teachers I have ever had.

Here is the low-down on Hummel: he is the hardest Chem 102 teacher there is because his tests are incredibly difficult but there are tricks to them.  Normally he tests on exceptions and often forces a student to read carefully, and if this is done the tests become MUCH easier.  He doesn't give joke questions for free points like Kelter.

Doesn't care about his students, and isn't very helpful or clear on things. I went to get help from him numerous number of times in the semester and did all of the assignments, readings, etc... and still struggled in that class.  Exams are ridiculously hard and don't even apply to the lectures.  He should re-consider his teaching technique.

This class was really hard, especially for someone coming in with very little chemistry background. The exams were ridiculously hard, and it seemed that he wrote the exams to trick you rather than to see if you knew the material or not. I reccomend trying Yerkes instead of Hummel if you can.

Hummel is pretty hardcore. If you haven't been introduced to the material before hand this class is difficult but doable (obviously). In order to get an A you really need to work and do ALL the home work. Overall he's a good guy though, and a great teacher. He cares about chemistry.
In two weeks, my high school teacher couldn't explain clearly a lesson he effectively teaches in one lecteur.

Lectures are a little on the boring side unless he's blowing things up or causing himself bodily harm while blowing things up. Nice guy, knows his stuff. Admits to being dumb in college but still makes his tests hard. You have to work to get an A, but its not impossible

Difficult class and difficult professor. Do not take  Chem unless it's requiered or you love it, because you will commit suicide if you take it as a Gen Ed.   He is pretty mathematically oriented on his tests, so if you're good at math and physics, memorizing and applying formulas, you should do well.
This is a hard class but Hummel is a good teacher and his lectures are very clear. You just have to put in the time.
No Comments

Great professor, really funny and does crazy things in lecture.  Tests are really hard, but he is very fair so it's easy to get a good grade(curve, plus he makes it so there are the same amount of A's in his class compared to the other ones)

Great teacher.  Lectures well and coherently.  Also knows how to have fun in class and keep the students entertained. The tests, while difficult, are very fair and if you but in some effort, you'll be fine.
he was an awful professor
One thing I have to admit, Tom is FAIR.  I came into the class intimidated by chem 102 being dubbed as a weed out class. But if you work hard it actually turns out a lot better than you may expect.
He's very helpful if you have problems with registration or class material. The past hour exams were all I needed to do well in this class. Tests are VERY comprehensive, though.
fun professor in lecture, does crazy stuff and cut his hand bad doing some weird experiment one day. tests are RIDICULOUSLY HARD! if u can get into 102A.
ridiculpusly hard tests
Well, I was registered for Tom Hummel's class, but I never saw him ever.  I've heard he was pretty good.  His material is pretty easy tho.
hes a really fun teacher who loves his job. he explains stuff a lot and makes it clear what you should know. he also enjoys blowing stuff up. very cool

Why isn't Hummel getting more love.  Of course this course is going to be a little tougher.  Go to 101 if it's too hard.  He does care and he makes it VERY clear on what the exams will be on.  Hummel is a great teacher who makes Chemistry fun and that's what everyone wants to have.
he is a cool guy and enjoys teaching. he also blew off part of his thumb in class so that was cool.

I thought he was a gr8 teacher, was very clear in what you should know and not know in his class, and gave a good idea on what his test were going to be like with the past hour exams booklet and then reviewed how to do those questions, so overall excellent teacher.

Hummel definitely loves blowing things up, he does so all the time. He seems a bit eccentric at times but lectures clearly and tries in earnest to make class fun.
